Commands to display the shell that the user is currently using:
  echo $SHELL
  echo $0

Keystroke combinations to exit the vi text editor
  :q
  ZZ

Commands to remove an empty directory, no longer in use:
  rm -r olddir
  rmdir olddir

Command to change group ownership of a file to _____:
  chown :____ myfile
  chgrp ____ myfile
  chgrp -v _____ myfile

Chmod command that would allow the owner to have read, write, and execute permissions, group will only have read, and all others will have no access:
  740

Command to create a physical volume out of an unused partition:
  pvcreate

Command to only see the last 10 entries in a log file named "/var/log/auth.log"
  tail /var/log/auth.log
